ib/Topology/Order.html#TopologicalSpace.instCompleteLattice\"><span class=\"name\">TopologicalSpace</span>.<span class=\"name\">instCompleteLattice</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/CompleteLattice/Defs.html#CompleteLattice\">CompleteLattice</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Topologies on `α` form a complete lattice, with `⊥` the discrete topology\nand `⊤` the indiscrete topology. The infimum of a collection of topologies\nis the topology generated by all their open sets, while the supremum is the\ntopology whose open sets are those sets open in every member of the collection. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Order.html#TopologicalSpace.instCompleteLattice","kind":"instance","line":186,"name":"TopologicalSpace.instCompleteLattice","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Topology/Order.lean#L186-L190"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Order.html#TopologicalSpace.gciGenerateFrom\"><span class=\"name\">TopologicalSpace</span>.<span class=\"name\">gciGenerateFrom</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/GaloisConnection/Defs.html#GaloisCoinsertion\">GaloisCoinsertion</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\